text: The Cassidy Farmhouse is located in Barneveld, Wisconsin. ==History== Henry and Sarah Cassidy were among the earliest settlers of Barneveld. The house was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1986 and on the State Register of Historic Places in 1989. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Wisconsin Category:National Register of Historic Places in Iowa County, Wisconsin Category:Farmhouses in the United States Category:Houses in Iowa County, Wisconsin Category:Greek Revival architecture in Wisconsin Category:Limestone buildings in the United States Category:Houses completed in 1860
title: Cassidy Farmhouse
